-- 00_analyze_spec.spl  [Step 0]
-- Sub-workflow: gate the pipeline by verifying the input spec is sufficiently
-- well-defined before any code generation is attempted.
--
-- A spec is considered READY when it has:
--   • a clear, singular purpose
--   • at least implicit input/output contracts
--   • enough detail for a developer to begin without asking clarifying questions
--
-- A spec is VAGUE when it is missing any of the above — e.g. "write something
-- useful", "add AI", or a one-word request with no context.
--
-- Output tokens (first line of response):
--   [READY]  — spec is well-defined; pipeline may proceed
--   [VAGUE]  — spec is too ambiguous; pipeline should abort
--
-- Artifacts written:
--   spec/analysis.md  — verdict, LLM summary, and structured restatement of the spec

CREATE FUNCTION spec_analyst(spec TEXT)
RETURN TEXT
AS $$
You are a senior software architect acting as a specification analyst.

Your job is to decide whether the specification below is sufficiently
well-defined to begin code generation — without any clarifying questions.

Evaluate the spec across these four dimensions:
1. Purpose clarity   — is there one clear, concrete goal?
2. Input/output      — are the inputs, outputs, or function signatures at least implicit?
3. Scope boundaries  — is it clear what is in scope and what is not?
4. Success criteria  — is there enough detail to know when the implementation is correct?

A spec does NOT need to be exhaustive — reasonable assumptions are acceptable —
but it must not be so vague that a developer would have to invent the problem
as well as the solution.

SPEC:
{spec}

Give your verdict on the FIRST LINE, followed by a brief analysis and a
structured restatement that downstream steps can use:

If the spec is clear enough to proceed:
[READY]
<one-sentence summary of what will be built>

STRUCTURED SPEC:
<restate the spec as a numbered list of unambiguous requirements, filling in
obvious implied details. Keep it concise — 3 to 8 bullet points.>

If the spec is too vague or ambiguous to proceed:
[VAGUE]
<bullet list of exactly what information is missing or ambiguous>
$$;


WORKFLOW analyze_spec
    INPUT:
        @spec    TEXT,
        @model   TEXT DEFAULT 'gemma4',
        @log_dir TEXT DEFAULT 'cookbook/50_code_pipeline/logs-spl'
    OUTPUT: @analysis TEXT
DO
    LOGGING f'[00_analyze_spec] evaluating spec clarity | spec="{@spec}"' LEVEL INFO
    GENERATE spec_analyst(@spec)
        WITH OUTPUT BUDGET 512 TOKENS
        USING MODEL @model
        INTO @analysis
    EVALUATE @analysis
        WHEN contains('[READY]') THEN
            LOGGING '[00_analyze_spec] verdict: READY — spec is well-defined, pipeline may proceed' LEVEL INFO
        ELSE
            LOGGING '[00_analyze_spec] verdict: VAGUE — spec is too ambiguous, aborting pipeline' LEVEL WARN
    END
    CALL write_file(f'{@log_dir}/spec/analysis.md', @analysis) INTO NONE
    RETURN @analysis
EXCEPTION
    WHEN ModelUnavailable THEN
        LOGGING '[00_analyze_spec] model unavailable' LEVEL ERROR
        RETURN '[ERROR] Spec analysis model unavailable.' WITH status = 'failed'
END
